The paper deals with algorithmic problems on graphs and their structural properties. Specifically, it considers problems that are polynomial time solvable in chordal graphs and investigates their complexity in graphs that can be made chordal by deleting at most k vertices. This fits into the area of structural parameterizations, which is a subfield of parameterized complexity theory. The paper also introduces a new type of tree decomposition that may be of independent interest. Based on these topics, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
